# The Big Picture

Your app consists of six main parts:

```text
User
   │
   ▼
Mobile App
   │
   ▼
Backend API
   │
   ├──────────────► Database
   │
   ├──────────────► Cloud Storage
   │
   ├──────────────► OCR Service
   │
   └──────────────► AI Service
```

Each part has a different responsibility.

---

# Component 1 – Mobile App

This is what users install.

Responsibilities:

* Login
* Upload reports
* View history
* Read AI summaries
* Manage profile

The mobile app **does not** analyze blood reports itself.

---

# Component 2 – Backend API

Think of the backend as the **manager**.

It receives requests from the app and coordinates everything else.

Example:

```text
Upload PDF

↓

Backend

↓

Store PDF

↓

Run OCR

↓

Save Results

↓

Call AI

↓

Return Summary
```

The backend is the heart of your system.

---

# Component 3 – Database

Stores structured information.

Examples:

```text
Users

Reports

Blood Values

AI Summaries

Notification Settings

Profile Information
```

The database does **not** store the PDF itself.

---

# Component 4 – Cloud Storage

Cloud storage keeps uploaded files.

Example:

```text
Report001.pdf

Report002.pdf

Report003.pdf
```

Large files belong here instead of the database.

---

# Component 5 – OCR Service

The backend sends the uploaded report to OCR.

OCR returns:

```text
Hemoglobin

13.2

HbA1c

5.8

Vitamin D

18
```

The backend then saves these values.

---

# Component 6 – AI Service

After OCR and user confirmation:

Backend sends:

```json
{
  "Hemoglobin":13.2,
  "HbA1c":5.8,
  "Vitamin D":18
}
```

AI returns:

```text
Simple explanation

↓

Overall summary
```

