# Monitoring

After launch, watch:

```text
Users Registered

Reports Uploaded

OCR Success Rate

AI Success Rate

Errors

App Crashes

Average Processing Time
```

These metrics help you understand how the app is performing.

---

# Logging

Every important action should be logged.

Example:

```text
14:02

User Logged In

------------------

14:05

Report Uploaded

------------------

14:06

OCR Completed

------------------

14:07

AI Summary Generated
```

Logs are invaluable when investigating problems.

---

# Handling Failures

Suppose OCR is temporarily unavailable.

The backend should respond gracefully:

```text
We're temporarily unable to process your report.

Please try again in a few minutes.
```

Avoid technical messages like:

```text
HTTP 500
Internal Server Error
```

Users shouldn't see server errors.

---

# Scaling

Imagine:

Today:

```text
100 users
```

Next year:

```text
100,000 users
```

Because your app separates:

* Mobile
* Backend
* Database
* Storage
* OCR
* AI

each part can be upgraded independently as usage grows.

---

# Disaster Recovery

What if:

* Server crashes
* Database fails
* Storage becomes unavailable

Prepare by having:

* Automatic backups
* Monitoring
* Recovery procedures

Planning for failures is part of building a reliable service.

